From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cppmega.mlx <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 15:55:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] tilelang: real T.fp8_scaled_matmul intrinsic for Metal + CUDA

Replaces the earlier frontend-stub patch with a working FP8 scaled matmul
that lowers correctly on Metal (and on CUDA via T.cast). Mirrors the
audiohacking/fp8-mps-metal scaled-matmul kernel (MIT license; commit
d4fbd40c48aa2a243e600d06627c7dd818150636) at the TileLang frontend.

Algorithm:

    @T.macro
    def fp8_scaled_matmul(A_fp8, A_scale, B_fp8, B_scale, C_local):
        for i, j in T.Parallel(M, N):
            for k in T.serial(K):
                a = T.cast(A_fp8[i, k], "float32")
                b = T.cast(B_fp8[k, j], "float32")
                sa = A_scale[0] if A_scale.shape == (1,) else A_scale[i]
                sb = B_scale[0] if B_scale.shape == (1,) else B_scale[j]
                C_local[i, j] += a * b * sa * sb

The macro relies on three earlier patches in this stack:

  - Agent C: storage-only FP8 emulation in codegen_metal.cc (the
    e4m3 subnormal decode helper now ships with the corrected
    e+7 biased exponent baked in -- see the prerequisite
    docs/upstream/tilelang_metal_fp8 patch).
  - Agent E: GemmMetalScalar dispatcher routing fp8 inputs to scalar fma.
  - Agent F-1: vector FP8 cast lowering (lanes 2-4).

Test results (cd /tmp/tilelang_apple_head/tilelang && pytest):

  testing/python/cpu/test_fp8_scaled_matmul_lowering.py     8 passed
  testing/python/metal/test_fp8_scaled_matmul_metal.py     17 passed
                                                          -----------
                                                           25 passed

Bench at 128x128x128 e4m3 per-tensor on M-series:

  TileLang T.fp8_scaled_matmul : 0.555 ms (0.008 TFLOPS)
  audiohacking ref kernel      : 0.172 ms (0.024 TFLOPS) -- 3.16x faster
                                  (LUT decode, no cooperative reduction)

Bench at M=1 N=K=4096 vecmat on M-series:

  TileLang scalar fallback     : 1.098 ms (0.031 TFLOPS)
  audiohacking simdgroup vec   : 0.182 ms (0.184 TFLOPS) -- 6.01x faster
                                  (simd_sum reduction)

The TileLang scalar lowering is correctness-equivalent to the
audiohacking reference at 1e-3 absolute tolerance for matmul and
5e-2 absolute tolerance for vecmat (FP32 FMA reordering across 4096-K
contraction). Performance work (simdgroup_matrix tiling, K-vectorisation)
is tracked as a follow-up; the current implementation is intended as a
correct, dispatcher-routed baseline that lifts the user out of the prior
"NotImplementedError" stub.

